    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Describe your issue\n\nThe documentation indicates that [the `profile` directive defaults to `False`](https://cython.readthedocs.io/en/latest/src/userguide/source_files_and_compilation.html#compiler-directives), which seems like what you would expect. However, in the C code injected into generated modules, the default value of `CYTHON_PROFILE` for non-limited API builds is actually 1. Is that expected? If so, why the divergence from the behavior of the directive?\n\nI ran into this in the context of https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/7050, which I would have expected to be impossible in a build without profiling manually enabled, but we turn out to hit because the monitoring function calls [are injected whenever `CYTHON_PROFILE` is on](https://github.com/cython/cython/blob/595ba7c9ebf071ce486d411a8b2384e5291a2239/Cython/Utility/Profile.c#L100). Of course, `CYTHON_USE_SYS_MONITORING` must be on too, but I would have thought that the monitoring support would only be activated if profiling was requested.",
