            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I think this is working as intended. Although may not be very well-explained.\n\n```\n# cython: profile=False\n... # code goes here\n```\n\nand\n\n```\n... # code goes here\n```\n\nboth generate absolutely no profiling code at all.\n\n```\n# cython: profile=True\n... # code goes here\n```\n\nwill generate profiling code. The profiling code can then be turned on and off by defining the C macro `CYTHON_PROFILE`. We don't say anything about the default for this C macro in the documentation, but it's on by default where supported.  That's been the case for as long as we've supported this I think.\n\nSo in the context of https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/7050, you must at least have the `profile` directive set somewhere in order to trigger this.\n\nWe can definitely document what the macros do a bit better but I don't think we want to change it, just because it's the long-standing behaviour that a lot of people are using.",
