            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "OK from some quick source debugging and you are correct, we are somehow hitting [this section to insert it](https://github.com/cython/cython/blob/595ba7c9ebf071ce486d411a8b2384e5291a2239/Cython/Compiler/Nodes.py#L2049). It seems like the profile directive is the one that's getting set now by inspecting the globalstate there (linetrace is false, profile is true). I'll do some digging into why, but in the meantime I think this issue can be closed. I agree that we don't want to change the default values for the macros, I wasn't proposing that since it's definitely a large change with a lot of historical precedent.",
